            <title>[LU-5824] auster -h gives wrong example</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-5824</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;% ./lustre/tests/auster -h
......
      -i N      Repeat tests N times (default 1). A new directory
                will be created under LOGDIR for each iteration.
......
Run all tests in the regression group 5 times using large config.

  auster -f large -g test-groups/regression  -r 5
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It seemed that the example should use &quot;-i 5&quot; rather than &quot;-r 5&quot;. Patch to follow.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
